Czech Equities Rebound From Lowest This Month, Led By CEZ, CME

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-02-18T16:24:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/czech-stocks-rebound-from-lowest-this-month-led-by-erste-cme.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark stock
index rose from its lowest this month, led higher by  CEZ AS , the
country’s biggest power utility, and television broadcaster  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd ., also known as CME.  The PX gauge gained 0.5 percent to 1,237.2 at the 4:28 p.m.
end of trading in Prague after falling 1.5 percent yesterday to
its lowest close since Jan. 28. CEZ jumped 1 percent to 817
koruna, its biggest daily advance in two weeks. CME climbed 2.4
percent to 340 koruna, its highest close since Feb. 9. Lender  Erste Group Bank AG  added 0.4 percent to 934.2 koruna.  CEZ, CME and Erste have a combined 54 percent weighting
within the 15-member PX.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  